$schema: https://usm.dev/schema/v1.json
$id: usm/mcp-write
$type: feature
$version: 1
$last_updated: "2026-06-22"
status: built
summary: |
  MCP write tools — let agents author and update .usm feature specs as part of the spec-first workflow. Adds draft_feature, update_feature, and update_feature_status tools to the MCP server, closing the loop between human discussion and agent implementation.

$system: usm/system
$service: usm/mcp
command: usm_draft_feature, usm_write_feature, usm_update_feature, usm_update_feature_status
intent: |
  The current MCP server is read-only — agents can list, read, search, and query
  existing .usm files, but cannot create or update them. The spec-first workflow
  requires the agent to write a feature .usm spec from a human discussion, show
  the human the generated markdown for review, then update the feature after
  implementation. Without write tools, this loop is broken: the human must
  manually write YAML, which defeats the purpose of agent-first authoring.

decisions:
  - id: write-tools-as-mcp-not-cli
    decision: Implement authoring as MCP tools rather than CLI commands only
    rationale: |
      Agents work through MCP in Cursor, Claude Desktop, and other tools. A CLI
      command requires the agent to shell out, parse output, and handle errors
      externally. An MCP tool returns structured JSON the agent can reason about
      directly. CLI wrappers can be added later for human use.
    alternatives:
      - option: CLI commands only (usm feature draft, usm feature update)
        rejected_because: "Agents must shell out, parse stdout, handle errors externally — MCP returns structured JSON directly"
      - option: File system writes only (agent writes YAML directly)
        rejected_because: "No validation, no markdown preview, no status transition enforcement — agents would produce invalid .usm files"
    consequences: "MCP server gains write capability — needs careful validation to prevent corruption"
    status: accepted
  - id: draft-returns-preview
    decision: draft_feature returns both YAML and generated markdown
    rationale: |
      The human reviews the markdown, not the YAML. Returning both lets the agent
      show the human the readable preview immediately without a separate generate
      step. The agent can also iterate on the draft based on feedback before
      writing to disk.
    consequences: "draft_feature is heavier than a pure YAML generator, but the review step is the whole point"
    status: accepted
  - id: validate-before-write
    decision: All write operations validate against the v1 schema before persisting
    rationale: |
      An invalid .usm file breaks downstream generators and MCP read tools.
      Validation at write time prevents corruption. The tool returns structured
      validation errors so the agent can fix them before retrying.
    consequences: "Write operations are slower due to validation, but prevent corrupt .usm files from entering the system"
    status: accepted

flows:
  - id: draft-feature-from-discussion
    name: Draft a feature spec from human discussion
    description: |
      Agent and human discuss a feature in chat. Agent calls draft_feature with
      structured fields derived from the discussion. Tool validates, generates
      YAML + markdown preview. Agent shows markdown to human for review.
    steps:
      - id: s1
        action: receive
        target: structured feature fields (summary, intent, flows, contracts, tests)
      - id: s2
        action: validate
        target: fields against v1 JSON schema
      - id: s3
        action: generate
        target: YAML string and markdown preview
      - id: s4
        action: return
        target: structured response with yaml, markdown, validation_status
      - id: s5
        action: observe
        target: agent shows markdown to human, human approves or requests changes
      - id: s6
        action: write
        target: if approved, agent calls write_feature to persist the .usm file

  - id: update-feature-status
    name: Update feature status after implementation
    description: |
      After the agent implements the feature in code, it updates the .usm file
      to reflect the new status and implementation paths.
    steps:
      - id: s1
        action: get
        target: feature $id or file path
      - id: s2
        action: update
        target: status field (e.g., planned → built)
      - id: s3
        action: update
        target: implementation.primary with code file path
      - id: s4
        action: update
        target: implementation.test_code and test_code_status if tests written
      - id: s5
        action: validate
        target: updated file against schema
      - id: s6
        action: write
        target: persisted .usm file with $last_updated bumped

  - id: update-feature-fields
    name: Update arbitrary fields on an existing feature
    description: |
      Agent partially updates a feature spec — e.g., adding a flow, revising a
      contract, or updating tests based on what was actually built.
    steps:
      - id: s1
        action: get
        target: feature $id or file path
      - id: s2
        action: merge
        target: provided fields into existing feature object
      - id: s3
        action: validate
        target: merged result against schema
      - id: s4
        action: write
        target: persisted .usm file if valid, error if not

contracts:
  - id: draft-validates-before-returning
    description: draft_feature must validate the spec before returning it
    must_have:
      - "Returns validation_status: valid or invalid"
      - "If invalid, returns structured errors with field paths"
      - "YAML is only generated if validation passes"
  - id: write-is-atomic
    description: write_feature must not leave partial/corrupt files on disk
    must_have:
      - "Validates full file before writing"
      - "Writes to temp then renames (atomic on POSIX)"
      - "Returns error if write fails — original file untouched"
  - id: update-preserves-unspecified-fields
    description: update_feature merges provided fields without losing existing ones
    must_have:
      - "Fields not in the update payload are preserved"
      - "Array fields are replaced, not merged (explicit intent)"
      - "$id, $type, $schema are immutable — cannot be changed via update"
  - id: status-transitions-are-sane
    description: update_feature_status enforces valid status transitions
    must_have:
      - "planned → in-progress → built is valid"
      - "built → deprecated is valid"
      - "built → planned is rejected (use a new feature instead)"

tests:
  - id: draft-minimal-feature
    setup:
      minimal_fields:
        $id: test-org/my-feature
        summary: A test feature
        intent: To test the draft tool
    expect:
      - assertion: validation_status is valid
      - assertion: returned YAML contains all required fields
      - assertion: returned markdown has summary and intent sections
  - id: draft-invalid-feature
    setup:
      invalid_fields:
        $id: test-org/my-feature
        summary: ""
        intent: ""
    expect:
      - assertion: validation_status is invalid
      - assertion: errors array contains summary and intent validation messages
      - assertion: no YAML or markdown in response
  - id: write-creates-new-file
    setup:
      valid_feature_yaml: true
      target_path_does_not_exist: true
    expect:
      - assertion: file created at target path
      - assertion: file content matches provided YAML
  - id: update-status-to-built
    setup:
      existing_feature_status: in-progress
      update_payload:
        status: built
        implementation:
          primary: src/features/my-feature.ts
    expect:
      - assertion: status field is built
      - assertion: implementation.primary is set
      - assertion: $last_updated is bumped to today
      - assertion: summary and intent preserved unchanged
  - id: update-status-rejects-backwards
    setup:
      existing_feature_status: built
      update_payload:
        status: planned
    expect:
      - assertion: error returned with message about invalid transition
      - assertion: original file unchanged

implementation:
  primary: src/mcp/write.ts
  test_code: ""
  test_code_status: none

see_also:
  - "usm/mcp"
  - "usm/mcp-validate"
  - "usm/gen-feature-review"
